art focus lecture postmodernism the wave events at stanford art focus lecture postmodernism the wave facebook twitter email print add to calendar wednesdays april 11 18 and 25 professor glen moriwaki's lecture series focuses on the profound impact of postmodernism on contemporary culture postmodernism the radical reordering of cultural values from warhol to koons the emergence and development of postmodernism from the 1960s to the 1980s transformed contemporary art the postmodernist aftermath the end of art having shaken the foundations of modernism the postmodernist wave appears to have run its course but its iconoclastic ideas and socially critical stance have permeated the culture what is contemporary art now art after 9 11 in the wake of 9 11 and the phenomenon of social media new forms and approaches seem to mark a shift away from postmodernism and its cynicism glen moriwaki a noted california artist teaches painting and contemporary art history at city college of san francisco he received his mfa in painting at uc berkeley where he studied with elmer bischoff and joan brown his book right now paintings by glen moriwaki was recently published by live worms gallery in san francisco when ongoing every week from april 11 2012 through april 25 2012 4 15 pm approximate duration of 2 hour s where cantor arts center auditorium map audience general public faculty staff students alumni friends members tags arts lecture reading visual sponsor cantor arts center contact 723 3482 admission cantor arts center member $75 non member $90 drop in attendance is offered for $30 on the day of a lecture if space is available no advance reservations are possible for drop in payment by check or cash accepted at the door permalink http events stanford edu events 303 30347 more info last modified january 5 2012
